data.abstract: <jats:p>We propose a multilevel correction method for the convection-diffusion eigenvalue problems which is suitable for not only simple but also multiple eigenvalues. Assume that there exists<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="M3"><mml:mi>l</mml:mi><mml:mo>∈</mml:mo><mml:mo stretchy="false">{</mml:mo><mml:mn mathvariant="normal">1,2</mml:mn><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mo>…</mml:mo><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mn mathvariant="normal">1</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">}</mml:mo></mml:math>, such that<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="M4"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>A</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>l</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math>is extremal for<jats:italic>Yang's</jats:italic>inequality; then we will give some conditions on other coefficients which can guarantee that every solution<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="M5"><mml:mi>f</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mo>≢</mml:mo><mml:mn mathvariant="normal">0</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:math>of the equation is of infinite order. More specifically, we estimate the lower bound of hyperorder of<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="M6"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>f</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:math>if every solution<mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="M7"><mml:mi>f</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mo>≢</mml:mo><mml:mn mathvariant="normal">0</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:math>of the equation is of infinite order.</jats:p>
